<p>Before a visitor reads your headline, before they understand your offer, before they've processed a single word — they've already received a message. That message was delivered by color. In the fraction of a second it takes for the brain to process a visual scene, color is working on associations, moods, and instinctive responses that have been forming since childhood.</p>
