<p>Amateurs choose a primary color. Professionals build a color system. The difference is the difference between a single instrument and an orchestra. A well-constructed color palette gives you primary authority (your dominant brand color), secondary warmth (the supporting tone that humanizes the primary), accent precision (a single color used sparingly for emphasis), and neutral space (the backgrounds and surfaces that let everything else breathe).</p>
